The paper deals with the index coding problem, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT) and network information theory (cs.NI). The problem is modeled using a directed graph, which falls under the category of data structures (cs.DS). The proposed interlinked cycle cover scheme involves optimization and graph theory, which are topics in machine learning (cs.LG) and social and information networks (cs.SI).
